>
  <p>A sports assessment with a cardiologist is important for practising physical activity safely. A stress test is performed based on individual characteristics and the intensity of physical activity.</p>

  <p>A sports evaluation is recommended when resuming sport after a prolonged break, for competitors or practitioners of intense disciplines such as marathons or diving, in case of a family history of cardiovascular disease, with symptoms such as chest pain or palpitations, with cardiac conditions such as hypertension or after a heart attack, after cardiac events such as surgery or stent placement, and for seniors and at-risk individuals with diabetes or obesity wishing to stay active.</p>

  <p>It helps prevent complications and maximise the benefits of sport on the heart, in a region like Valais where sport is an integral part of the lifestyle.</p>
